In a discussion regarding a faculty position at UCSB, James Rising received an email from Christopher Costello encouraging him to apply for an environmental economist role. Costello highlighted the benefits of the collaborations at UCSB, the interdisciplinary focus, and the Environmental Markets Lab. James enthusiastically replied, confirming his intention to apply and indicating he was compiling his application materials. He requested advice on tailoring his application to the search committee's priorities, and expressed interest in discussing the opportunity further. A draft response for James included a professional and concise inquiry about application guidance, along with a scheduling link for a potential Zoom meeting.
